1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:02,170
[Live and learn]

2
00:00:18,780 --> 00:00:19,710
Hello, everyone.

3
00:00:19,710 --> 00:00:20,780
I'm Zhang Junjia.

4
00:00:33,830 --> 00:00:34,530
Actually,

5
00:00:35,030 --> 00:00:36,260
I was so happy

6
00:00:37,170 --> 00:00:38,500
to see you again

7
00:00:39,030 --> 00:00:40,240
when school started.

8
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:43,240
Besides, I remember you used to
cry a lot back then,

9
00:00:43,470 --> 00:00:44,600
and you were chubby.

10
00:00:58,740 --> 00:01:00,310
The sound of heartbeats

11
00:01:00,330 --> 00:01:01,790
is like music,

12
00:01:02,360 --> 00:01:03,390
sometimes fast,

13
00:01:03,390 --> 00:01:04,650
and sometimes slow.

14
00:01:04,790 --> 00:01:06,290
When it loses its rhythm, one would
be uneasy.

15
00:01:06,290 --> 00:01:08,289
Just like the tenth fret of a guitar,

16
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:10,100
which is hard to play at first.

17
00:01:10,310 --> 00:01:12,370
But once you find the right position,

18
00:01:12,650 --> 00:01:15,090
you can play the clearest chord.

19
00:02:03,260 --> 00:02:08,100
[Smile After Tears]

20
00:02:08,289 --> 00:02:13,280
[Tenth Fret: The Chord of Heartbeat]

21
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:44,590
Junjia.

22
00:02:46,490 --> 00:02:48,030
Do you need help?

23
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:48,920
No need.

24
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:49,800
Go take a seat.

25
00:02:50,450 --> 00:02:51,010
Here.

26
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:51,810
There.

27
00:02:51,829 --> 00:02:52,520
Are you sure you don't need my help?

28
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:52,980
Yes.

29
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:55,230
Sit down.

30
00:02:56,370 --> 00:02:56,940
Okay.

31
00:02:58,440 --> 00:02:59,870
Are you sure you don't need help?

32
00:02:59,870 --> 00:03:01,310
I told you to sit down.

33
00:03:02,210 --> 00:03:02,740
Okay.

34
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,080
I've sat down.

35
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:06,840
Wait for me a moment.

36
00:03:18,130 --> 00:03:19,730
Tell me if you need any help.

37
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:20,829
No need.

38
00:03:30,570 --> 00:03:31,770
I did my best.

39
00:03:33,940 --> 00:03:35,810
I work every day to make money,

40
00:03:35,810 --> 00:03:37,810
so I just eat something to fill me up.

41
00:03:38,079 --> 00:03:39,680
I eat takeout almost every meal.

42
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,110
So,

43
00:03:41,950 --> 00:03:43,590
I've never cooked myself.

44
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:47,120
From now on,

45
00:03:47,590 --> 00:03:48,860
just leave this stuff to me.

46
00:03:48,860 --> 00:03:50,320
Aren't you still injured?

47
00:03:50,390 --> 00:03:51,790
Take care of yourself first.

48
00:03:51,790 --> 00:03:52,890
We can talk about the rest

49
00:03:52,890 --> 00:03:53,700
later.

50
00:03:55,930 --> 00:03:56,430
Okay.

51
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:02,670
Has

52
00:04:02,940 --> 00:04:04,870
the team training been going well?

53
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:07,610
My fingers are used to it now.

54
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:09,240
They don't hurt as much.

55
00:04:10,410 --> 00:04:11,310
What about you?

56
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:13,680
What about the basketball game?

57
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:16,550
I'm going for
a follow-up appointment today.

58
00:04:16,550 --> 00:04:18,120
The bandage can be removed today.

59
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:18,990
Don't worry.

60
00:04:38,540 --> 00:04:39,470
Wait.

61
00:04:42,010 --> 00:04:44,020
I feel like something's wrong.

62
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:48,540
Let's try again.

63
00:04:56,820 --> 00:04:58,880
I still feel like something's wrong.

64
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,610
One more time.

65
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:12,570
What's wrong?

66
00:05:15,180 --> 00:05:16,010
Junjia,

67
00:05:16,210 --> 00:05:18,730
there is not much time left before
the submission deadline for the demo.

68
00:05:18,730 --> 00:05:20,280
What exactly is wrong?

69
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:28,860
Well,

70
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:30,590
how about we take a break first?

71
00:05:35,330 --> 00:05:36,930
[Live and learn]

72
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:38,800
Are you okay?

73
00:05:39,030 --> 00:05:40,760
You seem a little bit off today.

74
00:05:44,070 --> 00:05:45,840
Can I ask you a question?

75
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:49,280
Back then,

76
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:50,710
why did He like music?

77
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:54,920
He was trained to

78
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:57,320
learn all kinds of instruments
since he was a kid.

79
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,690
Later, he liked composing songs.

80
00:05:58,690 --> 00:06:00,690
From then on, he began to love music.

81
00:06:02,460 --> 00:06:03,920
He felt happy when he sang.

82
00:06:04,860 --> 00:06:06,860
Is it really just because of the joy?

83
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,270
I really want to finish He's song.

84
00:06:18,470 --> 00:06:20,600
But I always feel that the current song

85
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:22,610
is just a finished product.

86
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:24,500
There is no emotion behind it.

87
00:06:28,350 --> 00:06:29,820
You mean

88
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,750
the current song sounds

89
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:34,520
like you're doing it just to get it done,

90
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,960
not because you really enjoy it?

91
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,070
Don't rush to find the answer.

92
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:50,070
Music is not an exam anyway.

93
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:51,310
It will tell you

94
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:52,540
on its own

95
00:06:52,540 --> 00:06:54,270
when your mind is most relaxed.

96
00:06:55,580 --> 00:06:57,310
This is what my brother told me.

97
00:06:58,810 --> 00:07:00,810
Sounds like something he would say.

98
00:07:19,470 --> 00:07:20,440
Diaoqin, are you okay?

99
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,100
I'm fine.

100
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,340
Do you want to take a break?

101
00:07:22,340 --> 00:07:23,040
No, it's okay.

102
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:23,700
I can do it.

103
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:27,530
Let's practice layups.

104
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:34,880
Jiateng, ball.

105
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:47,600
Junjia.

106
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:50,260
You're in such a hurry to play basketball.

107
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:52,320
Didn't the doctor say to take it slow?

108
00:07:53,230 --> 00:07:54,360
I'm just warming up.

109
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:55,440
Don't worry.

110
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,130
I'm almost done.

111
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:59,100
Let's go home together later.

112
00:08:11,990 --> 00:08:12,790
Junjia.

113
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:15,060
Can you get me a towel?

114
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:29,060
Don't move.

115
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:30,050
Let me help you.

116
00:08:32,299 --> 00:08:33,400
I can do it myself.

117
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,610
Is your shoulder okay?

118
00:08:37,010 --> 00:08:38,080
What if

119
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,510
it affects

120
00:08:39,510 --> 00:08:40,380
the game?

121
00:08:40,450 --> 00:08:41,780
If it really affects it,

122
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,520
there's nothing I can do.

123
00:08:43,990 --> 00:08:44,850
Sometimes,

124
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:46,220
accidents happen.

125
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:48,920
We have no choice but to accept them.

126
00:08:50,260 --> 00:08:51,160
But

127
00:08:51,630 --> 00:08:52,530
accidents

128
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:55,130
are always scary.

129
00:08:59,000 --> 00:08:59,870
You know what?

130
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:04,870
My fish have been replaced several times.

131
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:06,310
Before,

132
00:09:06,710 --> 00:09:08,420
some fish would jump out

133
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:09,810
and die.

134
00:09:11,010 --> 00:09:12,250
So I added a lid.

135
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:15,450
Unexpectedly,

136
00:09:16,620 --> 00:09:17,880
it was not ventilated,

137
00:09:17,990 --> 00:09:19,790
and the water temperature rose.

138
00:09:19,850 --> 00:09:21,310
Then, the fish died again.

139
00:09:21,690 --> 00:09:23,290
No matter how you prevent it,

140
00:09:23,690 --> 00:09:25,350
accidents will still happen.

141
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,400
But

142
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:29,350
I still don't want to give up.

143
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:30,630
One day,

144
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,670
I will definitely find a way

145
00:09:31,670 --> 00:09:33,170
to let them live well.

146
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,100
Find a way.

147
00:09:40,010 --> 00:09:41,870
Recently, during team training,

148
00:09:41,940 --> 00:09:43,870
I always felt something was wrong.

149
00:09:44,010 --> 00:09:46,180
It feels like I missed something.

150
00:09:50,970 --> 00:09:51,890
If

151
00:09:52,590 --> 00:09:53,650
you need my help,

152
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:56,010
I can be your audience.

153
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:59,220
I don't understand music,

154
00:09:59,830 --> 00:10:00,660
but

155
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:02,450
I can tell you

156
00:10:02,630 --> 00:10:03,960
how I feel when I listen.

157
00:10:26,550 --> 00:10:27,550
What was this song

158
00:10:27,930 --> 00:10:30,460
[Watching you drown in sorrow]

159
00:10:28,060 --> 00:10:29,220
originally about?

160
00:10:33,670 --> 00:10:38,090
♪ Watching you drown in sorrow ♪

161
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:39,530
In this song,

162
00:10:38,970 --> 00:10:41,650
♪ In your tears ♪

163
00:10:39,530 --> 00:10:41,070
He tried to talk about a sweet couple

164
00:10:41,070 --> 00:10:42,540
deeply in love.

165
00:10:42,580 --> 00:10:45,940
♪ I wonder what love is ♪

166
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,920
♪ It's when you're alone,
someone is by your side ♪

167
00:10:48,010 --> 00:10:49,710
I really want to finish it,

168
00:10:50,020 --> 00:10:50,910
not just because

169
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:52,280
it's He's last work.

170
00:10:53,350 --> 00:10:54,550
But

171
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:58,240
♪ It's when you're lost,
someone points out the right direction ♪

172
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:57,990
the more I sing, the more it feels wrong.

173
00:10:59,430 --> 00:11:03,990
♪ Though you have nothing,
you won't turn around ♪

174
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,130
♪ But you are in midsummer ♪

175
00:11:06,610 --> 00:11:07,450
♪ In spring flowers ♪

176
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:08,230
Why

177
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:11,630
♪ In the aurora full of stars ♪

178
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:10,830
can't I get that feeling?

179
00:11:15,390 --> 00:11:17,260
♪ I can only wait for you ♪

180
00:11:17,340 --> 00:11:18,540
Is it because your singing

181
00:11:18,540 --> 00:11:20,720
♪ I can't be afraid of you getting hurt ♪

182
00:11:19,310 --> 00:11:20,940
lacks sweetness?

183
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:25,550
♪ It reminds us that
freedom is also a cage ♪

184
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:26,950
If you want,

185
00:11:26,270 --> 00:11:28,840
♪ Between us ♪

186
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,880
I'll help you find it.

187
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:32,260
♪ Repeating ♪

188
00:11:33,620 --> 00:11:36,520
♪ After you turn around,
I'll wipe your tears ♪

189
00:11:38,920 --> 00:11:41,770
♪ Hugging and hovering, only in dreams ♪

190
00:11:42,690 --> 00:11:46,970
♪ After you turn around,
I'll wipe your tears ♪

191
00:11:43,530 --> 00:11:44,790
It's said that

192
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:47,080
fish have a memory of only seven seconds.

193
00:11:47,950 --> 00:11:52,940
♪ Hugging and spinning,
in the room that doesn't exist♪

194
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:49,860
Maybe their love

195
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:51,610
only lasts seven seconds, too.

196
00:11:52,370 --> 00:11:53,740
It's short,

197
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:56,470
♪ Hope, hope again ♪

198
00:11:55,140 --> 00:11:56,740
fading quickly.

199
00:11:57,380 --> 00:11:59,160
♪ You have no tears ♪

200
00:11:59,380 --> 00:12:00,650
But the seven seconds

201
00:12:00,130 --> 00:12:04,170
♪ I'll smile from afar, goodbye ♪

202
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,580
are precious enough.

203
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:05,190
Why?

204
00:12:05,350 --> 00:12:06,750
Because love

205
00:12:07,220 --> 00:12:08,420
is love.

206
00:12:09,620 --> 00:12:11,330
Even if it only lasts seven seconds,

207
00:12:11,330 --> 00:12:12,260
it's real.

208
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:14,830
Even if it's short,

209
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:17,530
it's worth remembering.

210
00:12:24,710 --> 00:12:25,540
In the ending,

211
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:27,910
after searching all day,

212
00:12:28,910 --> 00:12:30,770
I still couldn't find the answer.

213
00:12:33,150 --> 00:12:34,150
Maybe I

214
00:12:34,680 --> 00:12:36,450
can never finish this song.

215
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:38,220
Don't give up.

216
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,290
I once lost five or six

217
00:12:40,290 --> 00:12:41,320
basketball games

218
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,520
and couldn't figure out why.

219
00:12:43,660 --> 00:12:44,660
But I kept trying,

220
00:12:44,660 --> 00:12:45,690
practiced hard,

221
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:47,560
and realized that

222
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,730
even though I failed to get an answer,

223
00:12:49,730 --> 00:12:50,990
I could still win once.

224
00:12:51,570 --> 00:12:53,800
What if you had kept losing?

225
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:55,070
Then,

226
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:57,310
I would think I was unlucky.

227
00:12:58,970 --> 00:13:00,700
Is it really okay to think that way?

228
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:02,080
You have to.

229
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:03,710
Maybe

230
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:05,880
you don't have to find answers.

231
00:13:06,780 --> 00:13:07,920
When the time comes,

232
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:09,580
they will reveal themselves.

233
00:13:34,270 --> 00:13:36,280
[Diaoqin]

234
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:06,170
I noticed you weren't home this morning,

235
00:14:06,170 --> 00:14:07,640
and you didn't come to school.

236
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,240
What happened?

237
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:27,830
Excuse me,

238
00:14:28,830 --> 00:14:30,430
have you seen Zheng Diaoqin?

239
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,730
He went to the hospital
for a follow-up appointment today.

240
00:14:32,730 --> 00:14:33,530
The hospital?

241
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:36,300
His shoulder ligament is severely torn.

242
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:37,040
He can't participate in

243
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:39,170
the National Youth Inter-School Cup.

244
00:14:40,210 --> 00:14:40,740
Let's go.

245
00:14:40,740 --> 00:14:41,670
Let's practice.

246
00:14:45,290 --> 00:14:46,180
[Diaoqin]

247
00:15:02,730 --> 00:15:04,530
The number you dialed is not answering.

248
00:15:04,530 --> 00:15:07,060
Your call is being transferred
to voicemail.

249
00:15:19,260 --> 00:15:19,880
Junjia,

250
00:15:20,780 --> 00:15:21,710
why are you here?

251
00:15:22,430 --> 00:15:23,370
Where did you go?

252
00:15:23,390 --> 00:15:25,250
Why didn't you answer your phone?

253
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:31,810
Why did you go to the hospital
without telling me?

254
00:15:33,060 --> 00:15:33,860
I heard

255
00:15:34,260 --> 00:15:36,190
you can't participate in the game.

256
00:15:37,030 --> 00:15:38,330
Your injury is so severe.

257
00:15:38,330 --> 00:15:39,590
Why didn't you tell me?

258
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:40,630
It's fine.

259
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:42,070
Just miss one game.

260
00:15:42,540 --> 00:15:43,540
It's no big deal.

261
00:15:43,740 --> 00:15:44,490
But

262
00:15:45,150 --> 00:15:46,660
if it weren't for me,

263
00:15:48,010 --> 00:15:49,940
you wouldn't have gotten injured.

264
00:15:54,550 --> 00:15:56,080
Don't say so much right now.

265
00:15:57,180 --> 00:15:58,550
Let's talk when we get home,

266
00:15:58,550 --> 00:15:59,090
okay?

267
00:16:01,220 --> 00:16:01,750
Let's go.

268
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:12,730
Thanks.

269
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:16,300
Junjia.

270
00:16:21,540 --> 00:16:22,340
Do you remember

271
00:16:22,340 --> 00:16:23,640
what I told you before?

272
00:16:25,550 --> 00:16:26,310
Some fish

273
00:16:26,950 --> 00:16:28,050
jumped out.

274
00:16:32,190 --> 00:16:33,590
Later, I added a lid,

275
00:16:34,490 --> 00:16:36,060
but the water temperature got too high.

276
00:16:36,060 --> 00:16:37,590
Then, I added a thermostat.

277
00:16:39,790 --> 00:16:40,660
In the end,

278
00:16:41,330 --> 00:16:44,060
the water temperature
fluctuated drastically,

279
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,090
and the fish

280
00:16:45,530 --> 00:16:46,500
might still die.

281
00:16:48,970 --> 00:16:49,770
So,

282
00:16:49,770 --> 00:16:51,430
accidents are just like that.

283
00:16:51,940 --> 00:16:54,000
They aren't caused by just one thing,

284
00:16:54,340 --> 00:16:56,480
but a combination of events.

285
00:17:00,310 --> 00:17:01,250
I had

286
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:03,430
an old injury here long ago.

287
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:05,540
I couldn't lift heavy anyway.

288
00:17:06,050 --> 00:17:07,780
It just so happened that the hit

289
00:17:08,020 --> 00:17:10,150
accelerated what was bound to happen.

290
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:11,130
But...

291
00:17:11,130 --> 00:17:11,589
Junjia.

292
00:17:12,190 --> 00:17:12,990
I lost

293
00:17:13,050 --> 00:17:14,500
several competitions

294
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:16,000
and only won once.

295
00:17:16,089 --> 00:17:17,780
But I never gave up.

296
00:17:18,030 --> 00:17:18,890
Do you know why?

297
00:17:20,470 --> 00:17:21,900
If I keep telling myself

298
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:23,500
that I've lost,

299
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:26,730
then wouldn't I be too
afraid to do anything?

300
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:28,590
Though I missed this time's game,

301
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,480
I can still participate in the next one.

302
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:32,010
If we miss one opportunity,

303
00:17:32,150 --> 00:17:33,750
there will still be new ones.

304
00:17:34,820 --> 00:17:36,050
The most important thing is

305
00:17:36,050 --> 00:17:37,380
that you're still here,

306
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:39,580
and you can start again.

307
00:18:00,710 --> 00:18:01,740
What the heck?

308
00:18:03,210 --> 00:18:04,780
Don't you think it's scary?

309
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:06,450
Not really.

310
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:08,140
It's pretty ordinary.

311
00:18:08,340 --> 00:18:10,740
Besides, aren't they ghosts to begin with?

312
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:12,390
Can we stop watching it?

313
00:18:12,730 --> 00:18:13,510
No.

314
00:18:14,220 --> 00:18:15,490
If we don't finish watching it,

315
00:18:15,490 --> 00:18:17,960
how can we know if you
can get any inspiration from that or not?

316
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:18,560
Fine.

317
00:18:23,630 --> 00:18:24,730
Here it is.

318
00:18:26,170 --> 00:18:27,070
Here it is.

319
00:18:30,370 --> 00:18:31,290
Why did you scare me?

320
00:18:31,290 --> 00:18:31,820
How is it?

321
00:18:32,140 --> 00:18:33,140
Any inspiration?

322
00:18:33,170 --> 00:18:33,540
No.

323
00:18:33,540 --> 00:18:34,740
Don't scare me again.

324
00:18:35,310 --> 00:18:35,840
Okay.

325
00:18:38,650 --> 00:18:39,810
Horror movies

326
00:18:39,810 --> 00:18:41,270
can get your heart racing.

327
00:18:42,090 --> 00:18:43,590
Sometimes when you get scared,

328
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:45,990
you accidentally get closer to each other.

329
00:18:46,650 --> 00:18:47,750
Or

330
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:49,190
try rollerblading.

331
00:18:57,960 --> 00:18:58,810
How's it?

332
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,800
I don't know how to skate.

333
00:19:01,270 --> 00:19:01,740
Come on.

334
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,060
Give me your hands.

335
00:19:06,910 --> 00:19:07,710
I'll help you.

336
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:12,010
Take it easy.

337
00:19:13,350 --> 00:19:14,680
It's unsteady at first.

338
00:19:14,950 --> 00:19:16,880
You need someone to hold your hand.

339
00:19:21,260 --> 00:19:22,330
I think I've got it.

340
00:19:22,660 --> 00:19:23,520
I'm letting go.

341
00:19:23,690 --> 00:19:24,160
Okay.

342
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:33,210
When you fall,

343
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:35,200
someone will help you up.

344
00:19:36,570 --> 00:19:37,730
Finally,

345
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,970
go see the night view together.

346
00:19:41,210 --> 00:19:42,710
Looking down from here,

347
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:45,100
you'll find the whole city

348
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:46,380
looks smaller,

349
00:19:47,650 --> 00:19:48,680
like blocks.

350
00:20:00,140 --> 00:20:00,970
I think

351
00:20:01,230 --> 00:20:02,490
I've found the answer.

352
00:20:03,830 --> 00:20:04,890
What's the answer?

353
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:06,400
I was afraid of

354
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,240
admitting it before.

355
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,270
After losing He,

356
00:20:12,540 --> 00:20:13,540
I felt

357
00:20:13,540 --> 00:20:15,080
completely lost.

358
00:20:19,850 --> 00:20:23,960
[Senior He]

359
00:20:21,450 --> 00:20:22,320
Good morning.

360
00:20:29,990 --> 00:20:31,470
Why did you do that?

361
00:20:31,630 --> 00:20:33,190
He gave it to me.

362
00:20:34,230 --> 00:20:35,430
What are you doing?

363
00:20:35,940 --> 00:20:37,660
- No, no.
- You can't take that apart.

364
00:20:37,660 --> 00:20:38,430
Later,

365
00:20:39,230 --> 00:20:40,960
I thought I found my direction.

366
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,270
But

367
00:20:45,210 --> 00:20:46,910
I was just going in circles.

368
00:20:50,340 --> 00:20:52,470
Is it like dribbling the ball in place?

369
00:20:53,610 --> 00:20:54,510
Pretty much.

370
00:20:54,980 --> 00:20:55,680
Except

371
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:57,410
no one is going to steal my ball.

372
00:21:00,350 --> 00:21:01,590
I'm the one

373
00:21:02,190 --> 00:21:04,250
who doesn't want to let go of the ball.

374
00:21:07,090 --> 00:21:08,760
What about now?

375
00:21:12,730 --> 00:21:13,590
Do you know that

376
00:21:14,130 --> 00:21:15,590
no matter how dark it gets,

377
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:17,230
there will always be light?

378
00:21:19,510 --> 00:21:20,240
I know.

379
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:23,880
But no matter how bright it gets,

380
00:21:24,210 --> 00:21:25,450
it will get dark, too.

381
00:21:27,050 --> 00:21:27,980
Athletes

382
00:21:28,350 --> 00:21:29,320
usually rely on rest

383
00:21:29,320 --> 00:21:30,780
to recover their stamina.

384
00:21:32,590 --> 00:21:33,850
The sun needs rest too.

385
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:36,380
If it's always bright,

386
00:21:36,790 --> 00:21:37,520
the plants

387
00:21:37,890 --> 00:21:39,090
would wither and die.

388
00:21:39,790 --> 00:21:40,660
The rivers

389
00:21:40,930 --> 00:21:41,860
would dry up too.

390
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:52,110
When I'm with you,

391
00:21:52,310 --> 00:21:53,610
I feel recharged.

392
00:21:59,780 --> 00:22:00,310
Then,

393
00:22:00,850 --> 00:22:01,880
do you want to take this chance

394
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:03,410
to write down this feeling?

395
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:10,410
Here?

396
00:22:12,280 --> 00:22:14,440
The most real feeling is right now.

397
00:22:24,430 --> 00:22:25,490
This time,

398
00:22:25,570 --> 00:22:26,820
what I want to write

399
00:22:26,850 --> 00:22:28,270
is not what I lost,

400
00:22:28,690 --> 00:22:29,500
but

401
00:22:29,710 --> 00:22:30,840
what else I can give.

402
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:15,540
Our demo passed.

403
00:25:14,650 --> 00:25:17,940
[Preview of the Next Episode]

404
00:25:15,540 --> 00:25:16,510
We advanced.

405
00:25:18,110 --> 00:25:18,880
Welcome.

406
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:20,410
Is this

407
00:25:20,410 --> 00:25:22,120
where Junjia works?

408
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:30,890
Are you Diaoqin?

409
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:31,630
I am.

410
00:25:31,650 --> 00:25:33,150
Are you with Junjia?

411
00:25:33,550 --> 00:25:35,000
He hasn't arrived backstage yet.

